{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The place was completely empty, not a stick of furniture-- nothing, OK?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All the kids, the counsellors, through the organization, we started scrounging.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The boys from the-- from the cabinetmaker shop, they started getting tools in there.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We started making benches and tables and somehow they scrounged up beds.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after about three or four months, we all had beds to sleep in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't have to sleep on the floors anymore.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Chateau Montintin, they had an sort of an ancillary house, which was removed by, maybe, oh, an eighth of a mile.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it was within a five-minute walk.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a little house, and they called it Le Chevrette, which means a little goat, actually.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the kids from the orthodox home, from Eaubonne, were placed in La Chevrette.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the kids from the other homes, which were the less orthodox, or the non-orthodox, were placed in the Chateau Montintin.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But the whole complex was called Chateau Montintin.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was in the house, which had four bedrooms for the boys, and three bedrooms for the girls.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was an average of six people to each room.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So there were approximately 40 of us sleeping in this one little house.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there, the life, again, changed very, very radically.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The food was very sparse.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were pretty much always hungry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Meat was nonexistent.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was a vegetable, which is sort of a turnip, called [FRENCH], which the French farmers used to feed to their pigs, but we ate a lot of those.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, we ate what we call [FRENCH], which is sort of a grass type, a leafy type grass.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We had one of the-- excuse me-- the counselors, who came there, by the way, were in the same boat that we were.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were all refugees.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
